          <unittitle encodinganalog="title">
            <title render="italic">Scranton</title>
          </unittitle>
          <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian" encodinganalog="date">2002</unitdate>
          <physdesc>
            <genreform>DVD</genreform>
          </physdesc>
        </did>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="description">
          <p>A feature length horror movie about two brothers.  Albert, the eldest, is writing a book on the legend of an old town of which nothing remains save a derelict cemetery.  When Albert decides to spend a few nights in the town to finish his book he takes brother, Wallace, with him.  Strange phenomena begin emanating from the cemetery, eventually revealing the sordid secrets of the dead.</p>
          <p>Director: Channing Lowe</p>
          <p>Starring: John Woodhouse, Dennis Bott</p>
          <p>Music: Aaron W. Peterson</p>
        </scopecontent>
      </c01>
      <c01 level="item">
        <did>
          <container type="disc">2</container>
          <unittitle encodinganalog="title">
            <title render="italic">Old Hag</title>
          </unittitle>
          <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian" encodinganalog="date">2007</unitdate>
          <physdesc>
            <genreform>DVD</genreform>
          </physdesc>
        </did>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="description">
          <p>A feature length horror movie about a night crew in a warehouse who begin to have apparnetly paranormal experiences after the body of a famous serial killer arrives at the warehouse for storage.  Inspired by the phenomenon of sleep paralysis, also known as "old hag" syndrome.  1 hour 32 minutes.</p>
          <p>
            <title render="italic">Old Hag</title> premiered in 2007 at the Chicago Horror Film Festival.</p>
          <p>Director: Channing Lowe</p>
          <p>Producer: Steve Darling, Matt Keddington</p>
          <p>Starring: John Woodhouse, Rebecca Larsen, Aaron Peterson, Andrew Jensen, David Candland, Ron Hammond</p>
        </scopecontent>
      </c01>
